t%2C%20American%20businesses%20are%20feeling%20the%20pinch.%20Ethan%20Frisch%2C%20CEO%20and%20founder%20of%20Burlap%20%26amp%3B%20Barrel%2C%20a%20public%20benefit%20corporation%20based%20in%20New%20York%20that%20specializes%20in%20fairly%20sourced%20single%20origin%20spices%2C%20said%20that%20he%20has%20been%20receiving%20emails%20from%20Canadian%20customers%20he%20had%20a%20long%20relationship%20with%20saying%20they%20will%20no%20longer%20purchase%20his%20products%20because%20of%20the%20boycott.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20really%20sure%20how%20to%20handle%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Frisch.%20%26quot%3BWe%20as%20individuals%20at%20Burlap%20%26amp%3B%20Barrel%20did%20not%20vote%20to%20put%20Trump%20in%20office%20and%20we%20do%20import%20some%20spices%20from%20Canada%20as%20well%2C%20so%20our%20supply%20chain%20is%20very%20intertwined%20with%20the%20whole%20tariff%20situation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20this%20could%20force%20us%20to%20buy%20less%20from%20our%20partners%20by%20introducing%20an%20extra%20level%20of%20risk%2C%20which%20really%20contradicts%20our%20mission%20of%20putting%20more%20money%20into%20the%20pockets%20of%20smaller%20farmers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELarge%20grocery%20chains%20across%20Canada%20are%20also%20spotlighting%20local%20products%20in%20response%20to%20patriotic%20sentiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20Sobeys%20Inc.%2C%20Canada's%20second-largest%20national%20food%20retailer%20with%20approximately%201%2C600%20stores%20across%20ten%20provinces.%20A%20spokesperson%20of%20its%20parent%20company%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEmpire%20Company%20Limited%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etold%20Business%20Insider%20that%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20around%2012%25%20of%20their%20sales%20came%20from%20products%20sourced%20in%20the%20US%2C%20but%20given%20their%20work%20to%20%26quot%3Bfind%20alternatives%20to%20US%20sources%20over%20the%20past%2030%20days%2C%20that%20number%20is%20expected%20to%20decrease.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMetro%20Inc.%20with%20around%201%2C000%20grocery%20stores%20in%20Quebec%2C%20Ontario%2C%20and%20New%20Brunswick%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Longo's%2C%20a%20family-owned%20grocery%20chain%20mainly%20operating%20across%20the%20Greater%20Toronto%20Area%2C%20both%20said%20they%20have%20rolled%20out%20an%20in-store%20program%20to%20label%20individual%20products%20with%20more%20salient%20Canadian%20identification.%20Local%20products%20are%20also%20being%20promoted%20on%20their%20websites%20and%20newsletters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20available%20data%20from%20the%20International%20Trade%20Administration%20shows%20that%20Canada%20is%20still%20the%20largest%20destination%20for%20US%20exports%20of%20high-value%20agricultural%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226221c2d5-2e30-4d90-81b4-563c3ce82d41%5C%22%3EDownstream%20effects%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEconomic%20and%20policy%20experts%20have%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20depending%20on%20the%20size%20of%20the%20target%20and%20the%20length%20of%20the%20boycott%2C%20the%20agriculture%20sector%20in%20the%20US%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecould%20suffer%2C%20especially%20under%20the%20current%20push%20to%20cut%20back%20on%20federal%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20going%20to%20hurt%20the%20industries%20here%2C%20there's%20no%20doubt%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Larry%20Gerston%2C%20professor%20of%20public%20policy%20civic%20engagement%20at%20San%20Jose%20State%20University.%20%26quot%3BWhether%20it%20will%20hurt%20more%20than%20a%20counter%20tariff%2C%20that%20depends%20on%20if%20they%20can%20focus%20on%20a%20targeted%20set%20of%20products%2C%20how%20serious%20they%20are%20about%20it%2C%20and%20how%20much%20the%20Canadian%20government%20supports%20the%20boycott.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20I%20see%20it%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-sparking-wave-national-pride-canada-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%